The annual interest rate of the bank offers 8.1%; however, since the compounded interest is daily, we will divide the interest rate over the number of days in a year to calculate the rate we will use. Hence, in every calculation of future value, the rate we will consider is the following:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &= \dfrac{0.081}{365}

\end{aligned}$$

Let's now determine the future value of the deposit after five years.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &= \$6,500\times(1 + \dfrac{0.081}{365})^{1825}
\\[10pt]
&= \$6,500\times1.499235135
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$9,745.03}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the future value of the deposit after five years is $9,745.03.**

Let's now determine the future value of the deposit after ten years.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &= \$6,500\times(1 + \dfrac{0.081}{365})^{3650}
\\[10pt]
&= \$6,500\times2.247705991

\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$14,610.09}
\end{aligned}$$

**As shown in our calculation, the future value of the deposit after ten years is $14,610.09.**

Next, now compute the value of the deposit after twenty years.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &= \$6,500\times(1 + \dfrac{0.081}{365})^{7300}
\\[10pt]
&= \$6,500\times5.052182222
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$32,839.18}
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, the future value of the deposit after twenty years is $32,839.18.**
